article.description: — Evan Kuhlman had a career-high 21 points as Evansville beat Northern Iowa 65-61 on Saturday.
article.headline: Kuhlman scores 21 to carry Evansville over N. Iowa 65-61
article.linkText: Kuhlman scores 21 to carry Evansville over N. Iowa 65-61
article.story: EVANSVILLE, Ind. -- — Evan Kuhlman had a career-high 21 points as Evansville beat Northern Iowa 65-61 on Saturday. Samari Curtis had 14 points for Evansville (4-5, 2-1 Missouri Valley Conference). Shamar Givance added six assists. Jax Levitch had eight rebounds. Austin Phyfe had 17 points and 10 rebounds for the Panthers (2-6, 1-2). Bowen Born added 12 points. Trae Berhow had a triple-double with 10 points, 10 rebounds and 10 assists. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
